# .gitleaksignore Template
# Copy this to your project root as .gitleaksignore
#
# This file lists files/patterns to ignore for secret scanning.
# Use this for genuine false positives only.

# ==============================================================================
# Documentation with Example Keys
# ==============================================================================

README.md
docs/getting-started.md
docs/api-reference.md
docs/examples.md
CONTRIBUTING.md

# ==============================================================================
# Examples and Sample Code
# ==============================================================================

examples/**/*
samples/**/*
demo/**/*

# ==============================================================================
# Test Files and Fixtures
# ==============================================================================

# Python tests
**/*_test.py
**/test_*.py
tests/**/*.py

# JavaScript/TypeScript tests
**/*.test.js
**/*.test.ts
**/*.spec.js
**/*.spec.ts
__tests__/**/*

# Go tests
**/*_test.go

# Rust tests
**/*_test.rs

# Test fixtures and data
tests/fixtures/**/*
tests/data/**/*
tests/mocks/**/*
**/testdata/**/*

# ==============================================================================
# Build and Generated Files
# ==============================================================================

dist/**/*
build/**/*
target/**/*
.next/**/*
out/**/*

# ==============================================================================
# Dependencies (usually already gitignored)
# ==============================================================================

node_modules/**/*
vendor/**/*
.venv/**/*

# ==============================================================================
# Specific False Positives (file:line format)
# ==============================================================================
# Format: path/to/file.ext:line_number
# Or: path/to/file.ext:line_number:commit_sha
#
# Add specific findings here after verification they're safe
# ALWAYS comment why it's safe!

# Example (delete these and add your own):
# docs/api-tutorial.md:45  # Example API key in tutorial
# config/example.yaml:12   # Template configuration file

# ==============================================================================
# Rotated/Deactivated Secrets
# ==============================================================================
# Secrets that were rotated and are now safe to ignore
# ALWAYS rotate BEFORE adding here!
#
# Format: path/to/file.ext:line_number  # Rotated on YYYY-MM-DD

# Example (delete these and add your own):
# src/legacy/old-config.py:23  # Rotated on 2025-01-10
# scripts/old-deploy.sh:45     # Rotated on 2025-01-05

# ==============================================================================
# Project-Specific Exclusions
# ==============================================================================
# Add project-specific patterns below

# MCP server example configs (safe templates)
# **/mcp-server-config.example.json
# **/mcp-config.example.json

# Terraform example files
# terraform/**/*.example.tf

# Kubernetes example manifests
# k8s/examples/**/*.yaml

# ==============================================================================
# NOTES
# ==============================================================================
# - Always verify a finding is genuinely safe before adding to this file
# - Document WHY each entry is safe (use comments)
# - For rotated secrets, include rotation date
# - Review this file periodically (quarterly recommended)
# - Remove entries for files that no longer exist
# - Prefer .gitleaks.toml allowlists for pattern-based exclusions
# - Use this file for specific file:line exceptions
